    {
      "step_id": "3177dc28",
      "step_index": 4,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) SAR REASONING (why these features matter for hERG)\nhERG blockers often bind in the inner cavity via:\n- **Cation\u2013\u03c0 / electrostatic interactions** between a **protonated amine** and aromatic residues (notably **Tyr652/Phe656** region in many models).\n- **Hydrophobic/\u03c0-stacking contacts** from **aryl groups** with the channel\u2019s aromatic lining.\n- **Appropriate spacing/flexibility** to place the charged center and aryl groups into complementary subpockets.",
      "tool_name": null,
