      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T19:50:25.534231+00:00"
    },
    {
      "step_id": "5dc2580b",
      "step_index": 5,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "How this molecule fits those trends:\n- The **secondary amine** is likely **protonated**, providing the **key cationic anchor**.\n- The **two phenyl rings** provide **substantial aromatic surface** for \u03c0/hydrophobic interactions.\n- The **linker length and flexibility** (multiple methylenes + rotatable bonds) likely allow adoption of a **binding-competent 3D conformation** in the cavity.\n- The **amide** and **nitro** increase polarity and may reduce passive permeability somewhat, but they **do not remove** the core hERG-binding motif; amide can also help orient the distal aryl ring.",
