    {
      "step_id": "933779f5",
      "step_index": 7,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 3) MECHANISTIC BASIS (how it would interact with hERG)\n- **Primary interaction:** protonated **secondary amine** engaging in **electrostatic/cation\u2013\u03c0 interactions** within the central cavity.\n- **Stabilization:** both **aryl rings** can **\u03c0-stack / hydrophobically pack** against the aromatic residues lining the pore.\n- **Conformational adaptability:** the flexible chain can \u201cthread\u201d the cavity and place the aromatic groups in favorable positions; this is a common reason flexible diaryl-amine scaffolds show hERG liability.",
